a component is an individual unit of encapsulated functionality that serves as a part of an application in conjunction with other components.
- there are six (6) characteristics of components
	- reusable: implies that components should be designed such that they can be reused in different application.
	- replaceable: should be easily replaced with another component.
	- independent: the component shall be designed so it doesn't have dependencies on other components.
	- extensible: extensibility entails the ability to add behavior to a component without changing other components.
	- encapsulation: consists of bundling a component's data and methods to hid its internal state, so it doesn't expose its specific implementation.
	- non-context specific involves designing it so it operates in different environments.
a component can also be the interface for a database, called a [[Science - Computer Science - Computer Software - data access object.md]], that switches the user to a different database without the application knowing about the switch.
a [[Science - Computer Science - Computer Software - controller]] is a type of component that determines which other components need to be called for a particular event.
a service is a type of component. It is meant to be deployed independently of the overall system.

